Colors
CSS rules are simple key-value pairs along with a selector .We can set Css rules to change color and set backgrounds.so here we will talk about Colors.


The Color Property
CSS is used to set the text color inside an element.

Syntaxp{color: red;}
Example

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Page Title</title>
  <style>
  h2{
    color:green;/*color property*/
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
<h2>Welcome To GFG</h2>
<p>Default code has been loaded into the Editor.</p>
</body>
</html>
Output:


Screenshot-(17)
We can set color for different elements

Types of color values :
Mostly common color values are used below:

RGB
HFX colors
HSL colors
The CurrentColor Keyword
RGB:
specify color using Red,Green and Blue values.

The rgb() function in CSS allows specifying colors by their red, green, and blue components. Each parameter within the function determines the intensity of the corresponding color, ranging from 0 to 255 or from 0% to 100%.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
 /* RGB VALUES */
#t1 {background-color:rgb(255,0,0);}/*Red*/
#t2 {background-color:rgb(0,255,0);}/*Green*/
#t3 {background-color:rgb(0,0,255);}/*Blue*/
#t4 {background-color:rgb(292,200,199);}
 </style>
</head>
<body>
 <p id="t1">Red</p>
<p id="t2">Green</p>
 <p id="t3">Blue</p>
<p id="t4">Grey</p>
 </body>
</html>

Output:

Screenshot-(18)

HFX colors
tells about the color using hex code .A hexadecimal color is defined by the format #RRGGBB, where RR (red), GG (green), and BB (blue) are hexadecimal integers representing the color components. These values range from 00 to FF.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
 /* HEX code */
#t1 {background-color:#ff0000;}/*Red*/
#t2 {background-color:#00ff00}/*Green*/
#t3 {background-color:#0000ff}/*Blue*/
#t4 {background-color:#ff0098}
 </style>
</head>
<body>
 <h1 id="t1">Red</h1>
<h2 id="t2">Green</h2>
 <h3 id="t3">Blue</h3>
<h4 id="t4">Pink</h4>
 </body>
</html>


Output:
Screenshot-(19)


HSL Color:
HSL (Hue, Saturation, Lightness) embodies a cylindrical-coordinate model for colors.Specified using the hsl() function, the format is hsl(hue, saturation, lightness).Hue denotes a position on the color wheel (0 to 360), with red at 0 (or 360), green at 120, and blue at 240.Saturation (0% for gray, 100% for full color) and lightness (0% for black, 100% for white) complete the definition.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
 /* HSL code */
#t1 {background-color:hsl(0, 100%, 50%);}/*Red*/
#t2 {background-color:hsl(120, 100%, 50%);}/*Green*/
#t3 {background-color:hsl(240, 100%, 50%);/*Blue*/
 </style>
</head>
<body>
 <h1 id="t1">Red</h1>
<h2 id="t2">Green</h2>
 <h3 id="t3">Blue</h3>
 </body>
</html>

Ouput:
Screenshot-(20)

CurrentColor Keyword:
The currentcolor keyword refers to the value of the color property of an element.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
#myDIV {
  color: red;
  border: 10px solid currentcolor;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<p id="myDIV">
It is a good paragraph.......
</p>
 </body>
</html>

Output:

Screenshot-(21)

Note:

We have RGBA and HSLA values for color also here A stands for alpha.

RGBA:
It is an extension version of RGB color value with an A alpha channel with it.

Syntax:rgba(red, green, blue, alpha)
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
#p6 {background-color:rgba(0,255,0,0.1);}
#p5 {background-color:rgba(0,255,0,0.2);}
#p4 {background-color:rgba(0,255,0,0.3);}
#p3 {background-color:rgba(0,255,0,0.4);}
#p2 {background-color:rgba(0,255,0,0.5);}
#p1 {background-color:rgba(0,255,0,0.6);}
</style>
</head>
<body>
 <p>RGBA color Value</p>
<h1 id="p1">GeeksforGeeks</h1>
<h2 id="p2">GeeksforGeeks</h2>
<h3 id="p3">GeeksforGeeks</h3>
<h4 id="p4">GeeksforGeeks</h4>
<h5 id="p5">GeeksforGeeks</h5>
<h6 id="p6">GeeksforGeeks</h6>
 </body>
</html>

Output:

Screenshot-(22)
HSLA color :


It is an extension version of HSL color value with an A alpha channel with it.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
#p6 {background-color:hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.1);}
#p5 {background-color:hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.2);}
#p4 {background-color:hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.3);}
#p3 {background-color:hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.4);}
#p2 {background-color:hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.5);}
#p1 {background-color:hsla(120, 100%, 50%, 0.6);}
</style>
</head>
<body>
 <p>RGBA color Value</p>
<h1 id="p1">GeeksforGeeks</h1>
<h2 id="p2">GeeksforGeeks</h2>
<h3 id="p3">GeeksforGeeks</h3>
<h4 id="p4">GeeksforGeeks</h4>
<h5 id="p5">GeeksforGeeks</h5>
<h6 id="p6">GeeksforGeeks</h6>
 </body>
</html>

Output:

Screenshot-(23)





